data.title: CET Central European Time Now
data.meta_description: What is the CET Central European Time in minutes and seconds? Current CET/CEST Time.
data.text:
Central European Time Now (CET / CEST)

What is the Central European Time now?

Is it CET or CEST?

European Summer Time begins in the Europe on the last Sunday of March and concludes on the last Sunday of October. This is due to the fact that during the warmer months, clocks are advanced so that darkness falls later.

Timezone Abbreviations

CET - Central European Time,

CEST - Central European Summer Time

EU Countries following the Central European Time Now (CET / CEST) time:

Austria, Belgium, Croatia, Czech Republic, Denmark, France (except overseas territories), Germany, Hungary, Italy, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Poland, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain (except Canary Islands) and Sweden.
